
    Tsunami alert after New Caledonia quake

        

    
        
                
                
            
        A 7.5 magnitude quake has struck close to New Caledonia in the Pacific, with a tsunami alert issued for coasts within 1,000km (620 miles).The quake struck at a depth of about 10km at 04:18 GMT, the US Geological Survey reports.The Pacific Tsunami Warning Center warned of possible hazardous tsunami waves within 1,000km of the epicentre.New Caledonia is part of the Pacific's "ring of fire", where many earthquakes occur.The USGS reported the epicentre of the quake as 168km east-south-east of Tadine in New Caledonia, a special collectivity of France with a population of about 270,000.
    
        

            

